uno.collections.queues

Interface Queue<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of an individual item stored in the queue.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoundedCircularQueue, UnboundedQueue

    public interface Queue<E>
    This interface specifies the Queue abstract data type with standard queue operations.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      E dequeue()
      Remove the front element from this queue and return it.
      void enqueue(E item)
      Add an item to the rear of this queue.
      boolean isEmpty()
      Check if the queue is empty.
      E peek()
      Retrieve the element at the front of the queue without removing it.
      int size()
      Retrieves the number of elements currently stored in the queue.

    • Method Detail

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Check if the queue is empty.
        Returns:
        true if the queue contains no items, false otherwise.

      • size

        int size()
        Retrieves the number of elements currently stored in the queue.
        Returns:
        The number of items stored.

      • peek

        E peek()
        Retrieve the element at the front of the queue without removing it.
        Returns:
        The front element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when the queue is empty.

      • dequeue

        E dequeue()
        Remove the front element from this queue and return it.
        Returns:
        The previous front element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when the queue is empty.

      • enqueue

        void enqueue(E item)
        Add an item to the rear of this queue.
        Parameters:
        item - The value to be added to the queue.
